summary: Since you have a BA in literature and say it's the reason you are sure Briemund is meant to be, what do you make of the fact...
question: Since you have a BA in literature and say it's the reason you are sure Briemund is meant to be, what do you make of the fact that the source material (ASOIAF) for GOT, has Tormund as a bit player, in his 60's and he and Brienne have never met.
answer:
1) I never said Briemund is meant to be. I said J*B isn’t. Reading comprehension is a virtue.

2) I’m so tired of people bringing up things from the books, when discussing the show. The books and the show are two different things. The show is based on the books, but isn’t following them word by word, if you haven’t noticed (again, comprehension.) Yes, in the books Tormund is 60 and he never met Brienne, but in the show he’s clearly younger and did met Brienne. I don’t see here anything worth discussing. No one is complaining, that in the books Missandei is only 10 and there’s absolutely nothing romantic between her and Grey Worm. Both couples are minor enough to not have any impact on the major plot. The fate of Briemund is open, but there is no reason for it not to happen.

summary: Watching GOT with my bf is hilarious. He watches it for the first time, for me it’s the second time. He chose every character I...
body: Watching GOT with my bf is hilarious. He watches it for the first time, for me it’s the second time. He chose every character I said I disliked as his favorite just to tease me. He now vouches for little finger but in a very genuine and annoying way. You have no idea how much I look forward to ‘how do you answer these charges? Lord Baelish’.
